08/03/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Six people, including two children, died in a fire that broke out early Tuesday (March 8th) in an Athens clothing store.
The victims have not been identified yet, but all are believed to be Chinese nationals.
It happened in the western Aegaleo area of the capital.
Fire-fighters spent over two hours trying to put out the flames.
(Ta Nea, SKAI, Ethnos, Kathimerini - 08/03/11)
